-- Serbia Will Ask Russia for ‘Budgetary Support’ Loan, Blic Says
-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 2012-07-24T07:37:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-24/serbia-will-ask-russia-for-budgetary-support-loan-blic-says.html
Serbia will ask  Russia  to switch
part of a loan approved for railway upgrades into budget aid,
Blic reported, citing Finance Minister-Designate Mladjan Dinkic.  Russia has approved $800 million for the rail upgrade and
“we have signals that a part, worth a couple of hundred million
dollars, will be transformed into budgetary support,”  Blic 
cited Dinkic as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
 gfilipovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
